{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1761764075,"nonce":"3mF6A2sN+7I7Dy62DycbpVRPm3A=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7Uonqo","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7412","origin":"github"},"title":"Handle GenArk genome assemblies (GCA_/GCF_ prefixed)","message":"## Description\n\nMax Haeussler warned about potential issues with GenArk genomes (those starting with GCA_ or GCF_ prefixes). Need to test wrapped MAF tools with these assemblies and add support if needed.\n\n## Background\n\nGenArk is UCSC's collection of genome assemblies from GenBank/RefSeq. These assemblies use different naming conventions and may have different database structure than traditional UCSC assemblies.\n\n- **Traditional UCSC:** hg38, mm10, sacCer3, etc.\n- **GenArk:** GCA_000001405.15, GCF_000001405.26, etc.\n\n## Warning from Max\n\n\u003e \"Great! I expect trouble if you use \"Genark\" genomes, so the ones that start with GCA_ or GCF_, let me know when you run into problems there.\"\n\u003e \n\u003e — Max Haeussler, Aug 12, 2025\n\n## Potential Issues\n\n- Different database naming conventions\n- Different file paths on UCSC servers\n- Different table structures\n- MAF file availability/naming\n- 2bit file locations\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Investigation\n\n- [ ] Research GenArk genome structure in UCSC database\n- [ ] Identify differences from traditional assemblies\n- [ ] Test current tools with GenArk genomes\n- [ ] Document any issues encountered\n\n### Testing\n\n- [ ] Create test suite with GenArk genomes\n- [ ] Test mafCoverage with GCA_/GCF_ assemblies\n- [ ] Test mafFetch with GCA_/GCF_ assemblies\n- [ ] Test mafFrags with GCA_/GCF_ assemblies\n- [ ] Test mafGene with GCA_/GCF_ assemblies\n\n### Implementation\n\n- [ ] Add GenArk genome detection to wrappers\n- [ ] Handle different naming conventions\n- [ ] Update file path resolution for GenArk\n- [ ] Add GenArk-specific documentation\n\n### Coordination\n\n- [ ] Contact Maximilian when issues arise\n- [ ] Work with UCSC team on any database changes needed\n- [ ] Document workarounds or limitations\n\n## Example GenArk Genomes to Test\n\n- GCA_000001405.15 (Human GRCh38)\n- GCF_000001405.40 (Human GRCh38 RefSeq)\n- GCA_000001635.9 (Mouse GRCm39)\n- (Add more as identified by users)\n\n## References\n\n- Email from Maximilian Haeussler, Aug 12, 2025\n- GenArk information: https://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgGateway?db=hub_3671779_GCA_024586295.1","files":null}]}